1
00:00:18,813 --> 00:00:20,438
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:25,188
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:27,313 --> 00:00:28,938
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:31,147 --> 00:00:33,063
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:35,313 --> 00:00:37,147
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:38,938 --> 00:00:41,998
(Jirol / Kim Nam-soo, Mr. Kim / Song Won-soo, Chairman Lee /
Choi Sang-hak) (Officer Sin / Im Chang-seop, Mina / Heo Ye-seul)

7
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,438
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 3)

8
00:00:47,897 --> 00:00:49,438
(The Secret of Wooju Bakery)

9
00:01:14,772 --> 00:01:15,772
Are you crazy?

10
00:01:43,397 --> 00:01:47,022
(Wooju Bakery)

11
00:01:51,688 --> 00:01:53,147
What are you guys doing?

12
00:01:53,813 --> 00:01:55,248
Looks like they're fixing a broken engine.

13
00:01:55,272 --> 00:01:56,397
What are you talking about?

14
00:01:56,522 --> 00:01:59,188
Our spaceship runs on plasma energy.

15
00:01:59,313 --> 00:02:01,313
The balance is off. We
need sound waves to fix it.

16
00:02:06,105 --> 00:02:07,105
Hachi!

17
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:11,563
How did they get here?

18
00:02:11,688 --> 00:02:12,813
Huh?

19
00:02:16,188 --> 00:02:17,230
Hachi!

20
00:02:17,355 --> 00:02:18,355
Found it.

21
00:02:18,730 --> 00:02:20,147
What's going on? What happened?

22
00:02:21,647 --> 00:02:22,855
Finally!

23
00:02:27,563 --> 00:02:29,313
I can use this to fix the machine.

24
00:02:58,563 --> 00:02:59,980
Not bad.

25
00:03:00,897 --> 00:03:04,980
But how do you knead
the dough without a recipe?

26
00:03:05,105 --> 00:03:07,355
I told you, I have taste buds in my hands.

27
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:09,581
They're five times more
sensitive than your tongues.

28
00:03:09,605 --> 00:03:11,397
So I don't even need to taste-test.

29
00:03:13,147 --> 00:03:14,355
That's impressive.

30
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:24,730
That's why I don't want to share my secret.

31
00:03:27,147 --> 00:03:28,827
But if you really want it, I can tell you.

32
00:03:31,188 --> 00:03:32,647
Don't expect a free lesson.

33
00:03:33,563 --> 00:03:35,563
If you give me the recipe,

34
00:03:36,522 --> 00:03:38,272
I'll cut the final payment in half.

35
00:03:38,397 --> 00:03:39,605
Six months!

36
00:04:11,438 --> 00:04:12,980
Back off a little.

37
00:04:33,438 --> 00:04:34,563
Chairman.

38
00:04:36,355 --> 00:04:38,188
Please look at this.

39
00:04:39,688 --> 00:04:40,688
What is this?

40
00:04:40,772 --> 00:04:42,438
It seems there's trouble at Wooju Bakery.

41
00:04:42,563 --> 00:04:44,022
Let's go, now.

42
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,647
Yes, understood.

43
00:04:48,855 --> 00:04:50,313
It's really true, ahjussi!

44
00:04:50,438 --> 00:04:54,897
- I told you, I'm not an old man.
- Whatever, I'm not lying.

45
00:04:55,272 --> 00:04:56,022
Chief Choi.

46
00:04:56,147 --> 00:04:57,272
I'm back.

47
00:04:59,855 --> 00:05:01,772
Wait over there.

48
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:07,563
See if there are any
aliens that look like that.

49
00:05:07,688 --> 00:05:10,355
Wait, this one looks a bit like it.

50
00:05:10,938 --> 00:05:12,230
It's actually cute.

51
00:05:12,355 --> 00:05:13,772
Oh my.

52
00:05:13,897 --> 00:05:17,688
Senior, I think we really need
to investigate this properly.

53
00:05:17,813 --> 00:05:21,063
If you start spouting that nonsense
about aliens and UFOs again...

54
00:05:21,188 --> 00:05:23,022
Get out of here, you're
giving me a headache.

55
00:05:23,147 --> 00:05:27,022
No, I'm serious. I don't
think that lady is lying.

56
00:05:27,147 --> 00:05:30,063
Enough. We have a
pile of cases to deal with.

57
00:05:30,188 --> 00:05:32,605
Go check out that recycling
center the woman mentioned.

58
00:05:35,813 --> 00:05:36,813
Chief Choi.

59
00:05:36,938 --> 00:05:37,980
Yes?

60
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:40,355
Who's that person you brought with you?

61
00:05:40,855 --> 00:05:43,605
He doesn't seem to have anywhere to go.

62
00:05:43,730 --> 00:05:45,480
So I brought him to the station for now.

63
00:05:45,605 --> 00:05:47,397
I've got plenty of space, okay?

64
00:05:47,688 --> 00:05:49,938
I came here because I wanted to.

65
00:05:50,063 --> 00:05:51,355
That's why I'm here.

66
00:05:53,313 --> 00:05:55,688
Is the police station your
personal playground?

67
00:05:56,313 --> 00:05:57,873
If you can play in it,
isn't it a playground?

68
00:05:57,897 --> 00:05:59,480
What's the difference?

69
00:05:59,605 --> 00:06:01,105
- Hey everyone!
- Be serious.

70
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:02,748
My friend is at the
police station right now.

71
00:06:02,772 --> 00:06:04,272
Say hi to everyone.

72
00:06:07,355 --> 00:06:08,688
I'm curious.

73
00:06:09,813 --> 00:06:12,480
What did that ugly woman do?

74
00:06:13,188 --> 00:06:14,730
What did you just say?

75
00:06:14,855 --> 00:06:17,355
You're the ugly one, how
dare you talk about others.

76
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:17,938
Unbelievable.

77
00:06:18,063 --> 00:06:21,397
Everyone, this ugly person
here for questioning...

78
00:06:21,522 --> 00:06:22,789
Actually dared to talk back to me.

79
00:06:22,813 --> 00:06:25,147
Wait, someone said he's handsome?

80
00:06:25,397 --> 00:06:26,688
For real?

81
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:27,980
Where is he handsome?

82
00:06:28,084 --> 00:06:29,876
I'm not handsome, I'm pretty!

83
00:06:30,022 --> 00:06:30,483
Oh my god.

84
00:06:30,507 --> 00:06:31,914
I'm pretty, okay? And who
gave you permission to film?

85
00:06:31,938 --> 00:06:32,813
Officer Shin.

86
00:06:32,938 --> 00:06:33,772
Yeah?

87
00:06:33,897 --> 00:06:35,498
Should we head to the recycling center first?

88
00:06:35,522 --> 00:06:38,147
Why are you taking my stuff? Give it back!

89
00:06:38,272 --> 00:06:39,688
Ugh, seriously!

90
00:06:40,355 --> 00:06:41,563
Let it go!

91
00:06:41,688 --> 00:06:42,188
So annoying.

92
00:06:42,313 --> 00:06:44,355
Wait! I'm coming too.

93
00:06:53,355 --> 00:06:54,147
It's the Chairman.

94
00:06:54,272 --> 00:06:54,730
Hmm.

95
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:56,855
What is that guy doing here?

96
00:06:56,980 --> 00:06:58,230
Who knows?

97
00:07:00,605 --> 00:07:03,355
Well, well, long time no see.

98
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,789
We live in the same neighborhood,

99
00:07:04,813 --> 00:07:07,397
yet it's so hard to run into each other.

100
00:07:07,522 --> 00:07:08,647
Isn't it?

101
00:07:08,772 --> 00:07:11,855
Didn't we agree to pretend
we don't know each other?

102
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:12,813
Yeah.

103
00:07:12,938 --> 00:07:15,522
Since you both said
you'd leave Earth quietly,

104
00:07:15,647 --> 00:07:17,938
I promised I wouldn't
interfere with your plans.

105
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:20,873
You said you were
going to fix the spaceship,

106
00:07:20,897 --> 00:07:22,373
and I even set up a workshop for you.

107
00:07:22,397 --> 00:07:26,272
Why did you steal all the
spaceships that landed on Earth?

108
00:07:26,397 --> 00:07:27,980
This isn't a workshop.

109
00:07:28,105 --> 00:07:28,980
It's a construction site!

110
00:07:29,105 --> 00:07:31,355
Give us back our spaceship!

111
00:07:36,063 --> 00:07:38,313
That's not the deal we made.

112
00:07:38,938 --> 00:07:42,105
Just fix the Wooju Bakery building.

113
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:45,480
Then I'll return the ship
and give you the parts.

114
00:07:45,605 --> 00:07:46,685
You didn't forget, did you?

115
00:07:46,772 --> 00:07:48,772
That Wooju Bakery building...

116
00:07:48,897 --> 00:07:50,897
It's not just some ordinary machine.

117
00:07:51,022 --> 00:07:52,622
You should know that better than anyone.

118
00:07:52,688 --> 00:07:54,522
It's a living organism.

119
00:07:54,647 --> 00:07:55,647
A living organism!

120
00:07:55,688 --> 00:07:58,230
You can't just patch it up.

121
00:07:58,355 --> 00:07:59,480
It needs proper treatment.

122
00:07:59,605 --> 00:08:01,730
Then go! Go treat it!

123
00:08:01,855 --> 00:08:06,623
But then why did you kidnap...
the guy who was trying to ruin the bakery?

124
00:08:06,647 --> 00:08:07,855
That...

125
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:09,813
Do you have proof that we did it?

126
00:08:09,938 --> 00:08:11,748
I checked all the security
cameras in the area.

127
00:08:11,772 --> 00:08:12,831
You kidnapped someone
at the Chinese restaurant,

128
00:08:12,855 --> 00:08:15,897
and dragged them all the
way here. It's all on tape.

129
00:08:16,022 --> 00:08:17,355
Take these two away.

130
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,980
No, no!

131
00:08:19,105 --> 00:08:21,585
I really didn't know that YouTuber
was one of yours! Really...

132
00:08:21,688 --> 00:08:22,438
I told you to stop acting.

133
00:08:22,563 --> 00:08:25,043
- I really didn't know, okay?
- You should've said that sooner.

134
00:08:25,147 --> 00:08:26,313
I can't go, I can't!

135
00:08:26,438 --> 00:08:28,063
I'm all bruised up!

136
00:08:28,188 --> 00:08:30,813
- I can't, I can't!
- What do we do...

137
00:08:38,147 --> 00:08:40,230
Bro, the staff here are so handsome.

138
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:44,877
I can't even capture their movements.

139
00:08:55,188 --> 00:08:57,022
- Oh~
- Oh~

140
00:09:04,272 --> 00:09:06,938
Why are there so many
people all of a sudden?

141
00:09:08,355 --> 00:09:11,147
Isn't it good? We're making a lot of money.

142
00:09:11,272 --> 00:09:12,664
What are you complaining about, boss?

143
00:09:12,688 --> 00:09:14,772
This isn't the bakery I dreamed of.

144
00:09:16,397 --> 00:09:18,230
Then what does your dream bakery look like?

145
00:09:18,890 --> 00:09:21,313
It's not about having no
customers or not making money.

146
00:09:21,438 --> 00:09:24,313
It's a place where
people can come to relax,

147
00:09:25,355 --> 00:09:26,563
release some stress,

148
00:09:26,688 --> 00:09:28,605
and feel healed.

149
00:09:29,688 --> 00:09:31,522
That's the kind of bakery I want to run.

150
00:09:33,272 --> 00:09:34,456
Why are you looking at me like that?

151
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:36,897
Don't you ever look at the customers?

152
00:09:38,730 --> 00:09:40,313
Don't they all look happy?

153
00:09:45,105 --> 00:09:49,438
The only unhappy person here is you.

154
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:55,108
Scream, everybody, dance!

155
00:09:55,272 --> 00:09:57,522
Hi. Alright.

156
00:09:58,264 --> 00:09:59,764
Thank you.

157
00:09:59,897 --> 00:10:00,897
What's up man?

158
00:10:25,147 --> 00:10:26,938
You must be Prince Raon, right?

159
00:10:27,063 --> 00:10:29,522
I'm here to ask for your help.

160
00:10:30,313 --> 00:10:30,813
What's wrong?

161
00:10:30,938 --> 00:10:34,022
Two of our companions have been kidnapped.

162
00:10:34,188 --> 00:10:34,855
By whom?

163
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:36,688
They're alien criminals.

164
00:10:36,813 --> 00:10:40,105
They're wanted across the galaxy.
They're extremely dangerous.

165
00:10:40,230 --> 00:10:44,022
Ma'am, I don't know what your
relationship is with that human,

166
00:10:44,147 --> 00:10:49,563
but you should report this
to the police, not come here.

167
00:10:49,688 --> 00:10:51,522
It's not just us who are in danger.

168
00:10:51,647 --> 00:10:54,813
Those people are targeting the bakery.

169
00:10:55,688 --> 00:11:00,730
Targeting our bakery? Why?

170
00:11:00,855 --> 00:11:02,397
I'm telling the truth.

171
00:11:06,813 --> 00:11:10,453
"Today's Revenue: ₩13,060,800
Monthly Revenue: Approx. ₩41,818,600"

172
00:11:11,063 --> 00:11:12,313
Raon.

173
00:11:12,438 --> 00:11:15,563
It seems word has gotten out
that we're making a lot of money!

174
00:11:15,688 --> 00:11:16,730
My phone...

175
00:11:16,855 --> 00:11:19,563
I need to call my brother!

176
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:30,688
Brother! Something big happened!

177
00:11:30,813 --> 00:11:32,647
Some criminals are targeting our bakery.

178
00:11:32,772 --> 00:11:34,664
It seems the news about our
bakery going viral has spread.

179
00:11:34,688 --> 00:11:37,563
Really? Targeting a bakery?

180
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:40,230
- Yes...
- Who said that?

181
00:11:40,647 --> 00:11:43,105
Rap? What did he do with rap?

182
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:44,980
There are a lot of scammers out there.

183
00:11:45,105 --> 00:11:47,813
They're just trying to
scare people to get money.

184
00:11:47,938 --> 00:11:49,980
Don't worry, just stay put.

185
00:11:50,105 --> 00:11:51,813
I'll head to the bakery later.

186
00:11:51,938 --> 00:11:54,188
I'm busy right now, we'll talk later.

187
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,897
Who was that?

188
00:11:59,938 --> 00:12:00,938
Um... my brother.

189
00:12:01,063 --> 00:12:04,605
Don't answer the phone
like that for anyone else.

190
00:12:05,397 --> 00:12:07,480
Answering with that
handsome, gentle voice...

191
00:12:07,605 --> 00:12:09,397
it'll make people fall in love with you.

192
00:12:11,855 --> 00:12:13,438
I'm your number one fan, you know.

193
00:12:20,563 --> 00:12:27,188
You've changed. You would've
rushed over here before.

194
00:12:33,272 --> 00:12:36,063
So, they admitted it right here?

195
00:12:36,188 --> 00:12:38,730
That they're aliens? Is that what you mean?

196
00:12:38,855 --> 00:12:39,605
Exactly.

197
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:40,813
Officer Shin.

198
00:12:41,272 --> 00:12:43,105
That's enough. Let's go back.

199
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:45,188
Wait, what do you mean 'that's enough'?

200
00:12:45,313 --> 00:12:47,313
Are you saying I staged this?

201
00:12:47,438 --> 00:12:48,522
Are you questioning me?

202
00:12:48,647 --> 00:12:50,272
I didn't say you staged it.

203
00:12:50,397 --> 00:12:53,605
No, the look on your face... it
clearly said I was lying for views.

204
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:55,230
You definitely had that look.

205
00:12:55,355 --> 00:12:57,331
Are you looking down on
me because I'm a YouTuber?

206
00:12:57,355 --> 00:12:58,772
Who's looking down on you?

207
00:12:58,897 --> 00:13:02,647
The point is to figure out what
the aliens are doing on Earth.

208
00:13:02,772 --> 00:13:04,188
Isn't that the police's job?

209
00:13:04,313 --> 00:13:07,647
No, it's not just one or two aliens.

210
00:13:07,772 --> 00:13:09,706
A whole group of them
came to Earth to cause trouble.

211
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:10,480
Does that even make sense?

212
00:13:10,605 --> 00:13:11,605
Senior.

213
00:13:13,147 --> 00:13:15,105
I think she has a point.

214
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:15,772
What?

215
00:13:15,897 --> 00:13:19,480
Whatever conspiracy these
aliens are plotting on Earth,

216
00:13:19,605 --> 00:13:21,522
it should be up to us
police to investigate.

217
00:13:21,647 --> 00:13:23,039
We need to get to the bottom of this.

218
00:13:23,063 --> 00:13:23,897
Hey!

219
00:13:24,022 --> 00:13:26,102
Do you think the police are
the Earth Defense Force?

220
00:13:26,397 --> 00:13:29,855
Police are here to protect
the people, you get it?

221
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:32,605
Um, our conversation just now,

222
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:34,355
I recorded the whole thing.

223
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,397
Once I upload this to
YouTube, you guys are finished.

224
00:13:39,147 --> 00:13:40,230
Ugh, so annoying.

225
00:13:40,355 --> 00:13:42,813
Woo-hyuk, come here for a second.

226
00:13:42,938 --> 00:13:43,522
Huh?

227
00:13:43,647 --> 00:13:44,980
I said come here.

228
00:13:54,022 --> 00:13:55,480
What are you doing?

229
00:13:57,938 --> 00:13:59,605
Delete all the videos.

230
00:14:00,647 --> 00:14:01,897
Delete them now.

231
00:14:02,022 --> 00:14:05,355
Now, can you be my Seoul tour guide?

232
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:09,980
But are those two really going to be okay?

233
00:14:10,563 --> 00:14:11,563
Of course they are.

234
00:14:11,688 --> 00:14:15,022
I've already wiped that
conversation from their memories.

235
00:14:15,147 --> 00:14:17,438
Hey, you two over there.

236
00:14:17,563 --> 00:14:19,688
Yes, you.

237
00:14:19,813 --> 00:14:20,897
It's the police station.

238
00:14:21,022 --> 00:14:23,397
Just head back to the station.

239
00:14:23,522 --> 00:14:25,147
Alright, get up, get up.

240
00:14:25,897 --> 00:14:27,355
Yes, understood.

241
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,313
Alright, take care.

242
00:14:28,438 --> 00:14:29,688
Officer Shin.

243
00:14:29,813 --> 00:14:30,647
Officer Shin.

244
00:14:30,772 --> 00:14:32,647
Don't come back.

245
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,313
Handled?

246
00:14:37,438 --> 00:14:38,938
Everything is handled.

247
00:14:40,022 --> 00:14:41,272
So you mean...

248
00:14:42,147 --> 00:14:45,147
that the Chairman has been staying on Earth

249
00:14:45,688 --> 00:14:46,730
because of this bakery?

250
00:14:46,855 --> 00:14:48,272
I told you so.

251
00:14:48,397 --> 00:14:52,188
Could there be some
secret to this building?

252
00:14:52,563 --> 00:14:55,647
Actually, this place is a
massive mechanical device.

253
00:14:55,772 --> 00:14:59,272
It can generate enough
energy to destroy the Earth.

254
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:04,022
This place is not just a
building, I can feel it.

255
00:15:04,147 --> 00:15:06,938
Yes, it's a living organism.

256
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:11,605
Are you saying this building is alive?

257
00:15:14,063 --> 00:15:16,105
Did our ship crashing

258
00:15:18,855 --> 00:15:20,615
have something to do
with this building too?

259
00:15:25,605 --> 00:15:26,730
What on earth is this?

260
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:29,938
A harvester machine.

261
00:15:32,980 --> 00:15:34,063
Underneath Wooju Bakery,

262
00:15:34,188 --> 00:15:37,730
there's a device connected that
drains the Earth's vast life energy.

263
00:15:37,855 --> 00:15:40,063
The Chairman planned
to sell that energy secretly

264
00:15:40,188 --> 00:15:41,730
and make a fortune.

265
00:15:44,647 --> 00:15:46,367
Luckily, it stopped operating 15 years ago.

266
00:15:46,438 --> 00:15:48,522
But if it starts up again,

267
00:15:48,647 --> 00:15:51,313
all of Earth will be in danger.

268
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:53,355
I like ittt!

269
00:15:57,105 --> 00:15:59,022
Um, Your Highness... no, wait.

270
00:15:59,938 --> 00:16:02,355
What should I call you?

271
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,897
My name is Q.

272
00:16:05,105 --> 00:16:08,897
But... why aren't you going
home? Why are you still here?

273
00:16:09,022 --> 00:16:10,563
Didn't I just say?

274
00:16:10,688 --> 00:16:14,480
I don't know anyone here,
and I have nowhere to go.

275
00:16:16,188 --> 00:16:18,063
So what are you going to do now?

276
00:16:21,522 --> 00:16:23,480
Do you want to be my tour guide?

277
00:16:25,147 --> 00:16:29,105
I'm a police officer, not a tour guide.

278
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:30,897
Senior, look at this.

279
00:16:31,022 --> 00:16:32,813
We've already received several reports.

280
00:16:32,938 --> 00:16:37,438
They all say a UFO landed
in our area this afternoon.

281
00:16:37,563 --> 00:16:39,063
What did the Chief say?

282
00:16:39,188 --> 00:16:40,522
He told us to ignore it.

283
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:42,480
Just do as the Chief says.

284
00:16:42,605 --> 00:16:44,355
I just feel like something is off.

285
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,397
Like the fire at Wooju
Bakery the other day.

286
00:16:46,522 --> 00:16:48,730
I think aliens really have
come to our neighborhood.

287
00:16:49,230 --> 00:16:51,522
Didn't I tell you to stop
reading so many sci-fi comics?

288
00:16:52,438 --> 00:16:53,813
Senior!

289
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:57,563
NASA is investigating
the alien situation too.

290
00:16:57,688 --> 00:17:01,105
Even though many people
think it's just a conspiracy theory,

291
00:17:01,230 --> 00:17:04,647
I heard they come to Earth often

292
00:17:04,772 --> 00:17:06,647
to abduct humans for experiments.

293
00:17:08,605 --> 00:17:09,813
Aliens...

294
00:17:10,313 --> 00:17:12,063
are they going to abduct Earthlings?

295
00:17:12,188 --> 00:17:13,938
Ah...

296
00:17:14,438 --> 00:17:16,022
Well, I guess...

297
00:17:16,147 --> 00:17:19,688
there are some Earthlings who
are worth abducting, I suppose.

298
00:17:20,397 --> 00:17:21,730
But...

299
00:17:21,855 --> 00:17:24,397
Why is this person here?

300
00:17:24,897 --> 00:17:27,022
It's a bit complicated.

301
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:29,331
He's from abroad and doesn't
seem to have anywhere to go.

302
00:17:29,355 --> 00:17:32,147
Which country? His Korean is so good.

303
00:17:32,855 --> 00:17:33,522
Um...

304
00:17:33,647 --> 00:17:35,647
It's Thailand, right?

305
00:17:36,397 --> 00:17:37,438
No.

306
00:17:37,563 --> 00:17:43,188
I come from a distant planet without love.

307
00:17:43,313 --> 00:17:45,563
I'm a traveler,

308
00:17:45,688 --> 00:17:47,605
searching for love.

309
00:17:59,688 --> 00:18:01,230
Why are you looking at me like that?

310
00:18:01,355 --> 00:18:02,355
Nothing.

311
00:18:10,105 --> 00:18:11,105
That was a bit dramatic.

312
00:18:11,188 --> 00:18:12,813
This place looks like a new nightclub.

313
00:18:12,938 --> 00:18:14,206
Looks like a popular spot to take photos.

314
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:16,605
I heard it's the weirdest
bakery in the world.

315
00:18:16,730 --> 00:18:20,105
Like a bakery thrown together by aliens?

316
00:18:20,605 --> 00:18:21,938
Officer Shin,

317
00:18:22,397 --> 00:18:25,605
he doesn't seem to have a
place to stay. What should we do?

318
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:28,813
I've decided.

319
00:18:30,605 --> 00:18:33,938
I'll stay at the police
officer's place tonight.

320
00:18:34,063 --> 00:18:35,313
Huh?

321
00:18:37,605 --> 00:18:38,730
Not at my place.

322
00:18:38,855 --> 00:18:39,897
Yes, you can.

323
00:18:40,438 --> 00:18:41,748
Calling in a complaint,

324
00:18:41,772 --> 00:18:44,188
27-50 Wangri-dong, noise
complaint at the bakery.

325
00:18:44,313 --> 00:18:46,393
Patrol cars in the area,
please respond immediately.

326
00:18:50,522 --> 00:18:51,355
On our way.

327
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,355
Your voice is truly charming.

328
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,022
I like it.

329
00:18:59,022 --> 00:19:01,647
Earth is more romantic than I thought.

330
00:19:05,647 --> 00:19:09,605
Why are you waking up
the whole neighborhood?

331
00:19:09,730 --> 00:19:11,855
I'm very sorry.

332
00:19:14,355 --> 00:19:15,938
Police is here.

333
00:19:16,105 --> 00:19:18,188
It's so noisy here, it's driving us crazy.

334
00:19:18,313 --> 00:19:19,772
Can you do something about it?

335
00:19:22,188 --> 00:19:23,605
The kids can't even sleep.

336
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:24,272
I'm very sorry.

337
00:19:24,397 --> 00:19:26,373
(Wooju Bakery) I thought a bakery
would be quiet. What is going on here?

338
00:19:26,397 --> 00:19:27,522
I'm sorry.

339
00:19:38,272 --> 00:19:42,063
Could that be an alien memory eraser?

340
00:19:42,188 --> 00:19:45,313
No, it's more like a
dissatisfaction eraser.

341
00:19:46,438 --> 00:19:50,188
Alright, everyone go home
now. Stop crowding around.

342
00:19:50,313 --> 00:19:54,230
Boss, what were those people doing outside?

343
00:19:54,355 --> 00:19:55,355
I don't know.

344
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,980
They were making such a
scene just a moment ago,

345
00:19:58,105 --> 00:20:00,022
and then they all just left.

346
00:20:00,147 --> 00:20:02,507
Your fiancé was shooting some
weird thing around out there.

347
00:20:05,313 --> 00:20:06,313
Q.

348
00:20:06,355 --> 00:20:08,313
Are you using an emotion-regulating gun?

349
00:20:08,438 --> 00:20:10,522
Huh? What's the problem?

350
00:20:10,647 --> 00:20:12,938
Isn't that for erasing memories?

351
00:20:13,355 --> 00:20:16,605
You're one to talk, you
snuck onto Earth yourself.

352
00:20:18,647 --> 00:20:20,730
Wooju, are you okay?

353
00:20:21,647 --> 00:20:22,522
I'm fine.

354
00:20:22,647 --> 00:20:26,397
But the way they were
acting earlier was pretty scary.

355
00:20:26,522 --> 00:20:28,105
Sorry, Wooju. That just now...

356
00:20:28,230 --> 00:20:30,147
Don't contact Woo-hyuk anymore.

357
00:20:30,272 --> 00:20:31,730
Just come to me directly.

358
00:20:32,563 --> 00:20:36,063
I'll use that gun to take
care of everything for you.

359
00:20:37,855 --> 00:20:41,022
I'll be borrowing Woo-hyuk now.

360
00:20:41,813 --> 00:20:43,105
No!

361
00:20:50,813 --> 00:20:52,331
This isn't the way I want things to be.

362
00:20:52,355 --> 00:20:53,855
I said no!

363
00:20:56,063 --> 00:20:56,813
Boss.

364
00:20:56,938 --> 00:20:58,022
What?

365
00:20:58,147 --> 00:21:00,272
We earned a lot today.

366
00:21:00,397 --> 00:21:01,730
Do you know how much we made?

367
00:21:10,188 --> 00:21:10,938
What is this?

368
00:21:11,063 --> 00:21:12,647
I didn't even do anything.

369
00:21:12,772 --> 00:21:14,063
You...

370
00:21:15,772 --> 00:21:16,772
(Closed)

371
00:21:18,272 --> 00:21:19,938
Good work, everyone.

372
00:21:20,063 --> 00:21:23,605
Does anyone know where Q is staying?

373
00:21:30,022 --> 00:21:31,397
Can't he just sleep here?

374
00:21:34,022 --> 00:21:37,563
I'm not sleeping in this filthy place.

375
00:21:37,688 --> 00:21:40,438
You take him. It would be good.

376
00:21:40,813 --> 00:21:42,855
He can stay at my place tonight.

377
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:44,980
Bro, don't you only have one room?

378
00:21:45,105 --> 00:21:47,563
It's fine, I'll just sleep on the sofa.

379
00:21:47,688 --> 00:21:50,647
I'm heading out. Good work, everyone.

380
00:21:50,772 --> 00:21:52,063
You...!

381
00:22:07,397 --> 00:22:09,522
Don't stay over there,
come lie down next to me.

382
00:22:09,813 --> 00:22:12,355
No... no thanks, I'm fine like this.

383
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:15,022
I'm the type of person
who, if I want something,

384
00:22:15,147 --> 00:22:19,105
I'll chase it to the ends of
the universe until I get it.

385
00:22:22,563 --> 00:22:24,123
I really envy that confidence of yours.

386
00:22:24,230 --> 00:22:24,938
Why?

387
00:22:25,063 --> 00:22:28,313
Because I've never
gotten anything I wanted.

388
00:22:29,647 --> 00:22:31,313
That's perfect then.

389
00:22:31,438 --> 00:22:32,230
What do you mean?

390
00:22:32,355 --> 00:22:35,563
You'll soon have something you want.

391
00:22:35,688 --> 00:22:38,938
And it's the kind you won't
have to give up to anyone else.

392
00:22:47,313 --> 00:22:50,855
Is that toy gun really that dangerous?

393
00:22:50,980 --> 00:22:55,438
Yeah, it can control emotions,

394
00:22:55,563 --> 00:22:57,355
and it can also wipe memories.

395
00:22:59,063 --> 00:23:01,230
But it doesn't wipe everything clean.

396
00:23:03,313 --> 00:23:06,063
Huh? Wiping memories? Here we go again.

397
00:23:07,813 --> 00:23:09,522
We'll talk about it later.

398
00:23:09,647 --> 00:23:10,855
I'm going to take a shower.

399
00:23:10,955 --> 00:23:14,022
A shower? What's that?

400
00:23:14,147 --> 00:23:18,105
Wait, don't tell me... you've
never even taken a shower?

401
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:21,938
When my body gets
dirty, of course I wash it.

402
00:23:22,063 --> 00:23:24,438
But don't you use expensive
water to wash here?

403
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:26,397
Then what else would you use?

404
00:23:27,063 --> 00:23:28,313
Air.

405
00:23:28,438 --> 00:23:30,397
Wow! That's so gross.

406
00:23:30,855 --> 00:23:33,397
Doesn't that mean you're
not really washing at all?

407
00:23:33,522 --> 00:23:35,147
Move, I'm going to shower.

408
00:23:37,313 --> 00:23:39,230
Can I watch you shower?

409
00:23:40,772 --> 00:23:44,522
What the hell are you
talking about? Are you crazy?

410
00:23:45,688 --> 00:23:49,022
Because I've never seen
anyone shower with water.

411
00:23:56,563 --> 00:23:58,563
Didn't you say you'd never tried it?

412
00:24:12,688 --> 00:24:15,563
You're actually using water. How amazing.

413
00:24:15,688 --> 00:24:20,688
Don't get the wrong idea, I brought
you here so you could wash up too.

414
00:24:20,813 --> 00:24:22,133
Do I have to wash with water too?

415
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:28,355
Hold on, wait until I'm
done before you start.

416
00:24:30,813 --> 00:24:33,022
Can you soap up my back for me?

417
00:24:33,147 --> 00:24:34,730
Soap?

418
00:24:35,355 --> 00:24:37,105
Just like that, rub it on my back.

419
00:24:37,855 --> 00:24:38,897
Hurry up!

420
00:24:39,022 --> 00:24:40,647
How am I supposed to do it?

421
00:24:40,772 --> 00:24:42,563
Just rub it on!

422
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:50,313
You have the soap, right? Use that.

423
00:25:06,397 --> 00:25:07,688
Come on.

424
00:25:07,813 --> 00:25:09,272
Hey! Get a move on!
